Brazil Corn Crop to Fall Less Than Forecast This Year, USDA Says

-- B y   J e f f   W i l s o n
-- 
2011-03-22T19:20:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/brazil-corn-crop-to-fall-less-than-forecast-this-year-usda-says.html
Brazil  may harvest 53.5 million
metric tons of corn in the year that began March 1, down from
56.1 million produced last year, a unit of the  U.S. Department
of Agriculture  said in a  report  dated March 16 and posted today
on its website. The official department estimate on March 10 was
53 million tons.  Wheat output in the year that begins Oct. 1 may fall to 5.4
million tons, down from an estimated 5.9 million this year, the
agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Wilson in Chicago at 
 jwilson29@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 